=External links==\n;Official campaign websites\n* [https://rebeccaholcombe.com/ Rebecca Holcombe (D) for Governor]\n* [https://johnklar4governor.com/ John Klar (R) for Governor]\n* [https://www.philscott.org/ Phil Scott (R) for Governor]\n* [https://Www.winburn2020.com Patrick Winburn (D) for Governor]\n* [https://www.zuckermanforvt.com/ David Zuckerman (D) for Governor]\n\n{{2020 United States elections}}\n\n[[Category:Vermont gubernatorial elections|2020]]\n[[Category:2020 Vermont elections|Governor]]\n[[Category:2020 United States gubernatorial elections|Vermont]]\n", "text_old": "{{see also|2020 United States gubernatorial elections}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name      = 2020 Vermont gubernatorial election\n| country            = Vermont\n| type               = presidential\n| ongoing            = yes\n| previous_election  = 2018 Vermont gubernatorial election\n| previous_year      = 2018\n| next_election      = 2022 Vermont gubernatorial election\n| next_year          = 2022\n| election_date      = November 3, 2020\n| image1             = \n| nominee1           = \n| party1             = Republican Party (United States)\n| popular_vote1      = \n| percentage1        = \n| image2             = \n| nominee2           = \n| party2             = Democratic Party (United States)\n| popular_vote2      = \n| percentage2        = \n| title              = Governor\n| before_election    = [[Phil Scott (politician)|Phil Scott]]\n| before_party       = Republican Party (United States)\n}}\n{{ElectionsVT}}\n\nThe '''2020 Vermont gubernatorial election''' will be held on November 3, 2020, to elect the [[Governor of Vermont]]. As Vermont does not impose term limits upon its governors, incumbent [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] Governor [[Phil Scott (politician)|Phil Scott]] is eligible to run for reelection to a third term in office. On November 18, 2019, he confirmed that he was running for reelection, but has not yet publicly announced his campaign.<ref name=\"vtdigger.org\">{{cite news|title=Scott says he\u2019s undecided on 2020 \u2014 but he\u2019s already fundraising|url=https://vtdigger.org/2019/11/18/scott-says-hes-undecided-on-2020-but-hes-already-fundraising/|last=Landen|first=Xander|publisher=Vermont Digger|accessdate=December 4, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Republican primary==\n===Candidates===\n\n====Declared====\n* John Klar, lawyer and pastor<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://vtdigger.org/2019/10/28/margolis-rural-populist-and-gop-newcomer-announces-candidacy-for-governor/|title=Margolis: 'Rural populist' and GOP newcomer announces candidacy for governor|date=2019-10-28|website=VTDigger|language=en-US|last1=Margolis|first1=Jon|access-date=2019-10-30}}</ref>\n* [[Phil Scott (politician)|Phil Scott]], incumbent [[Governor of Vermont]] (2017\u2013present) (has not yet publicly announced his campaign for reelection, but is fundraising for it)<ref name=\"vtdigger.org\" />\n\n===Results===\n{{Election box begin no change\n|title = Republican primary results\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n|candidate = John Klar\n|party = Vermont Republican Party\n|votes = \n|percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n|candidate = [[Phil Scott (politician)|Phil Scott]] (incumbent)\n|party = Vermont Republican Party\n|votes = \n|percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n|candidate = ''Write-ins''\n|party = Vermont Republican Party\n|votes = \n|percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n|votes = \n|percentage = 100.0%\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==Democratic primary==\n===Candidates===\n====Declared====\n*[[Rebecca Holcombe]], former Vermont Education Secretary<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sevendaysvt.com/OffMessage/archives/2019/07/16/former-ed-secretary-rebecca-holcombe-to-run-for-governor-of-vermont|title=Former Ed Secretary Rebecca Holcombe to Run for Governor of Vermont|last=Heintz|first=Paul|website=Seven Days|language=en|date=July 16, 2019|acce