; Governors\n* [[Madeleine Kunin]], former Governor of Vermont<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sltrib.com/news/politics/2019/05/14/lt-gov-spencer-cox/|title=Lt. Gov. Spencer Cox announces he is running for Utah governor, vows a \u2018different,\u2019 positive campaign|work=[[The Salt Lake Tribune]]|date=May 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\n; State representatives\n* Tim Briglin\n* Kevin \u201cCoach\u201d Christie\n* Sara Coffey\n* Peter Conlon\n* Tim Jerman (former)\n* Martin Lalonde\n* Jim Masland\n* David Potter\n* Ann Pugh\n* Mary Sullivan\n* Maida Townsend\n* David Yacovone\n* Sam Young\n\n;Individuals\n* Dottie Deans, former chair of the Vermont Democratic Party<ref>{{cite web|url=https://rebeccaholcombe.com/supporters/|title=Supporter|website=Rebecca for Vermont|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = David Zuckerman\n| list =\n;Political figures<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.zuckermanforvt.com/news/2020/3/11/zuckerman-endorsed-by-democratic-party-leaders|title=Zuckerman Endorsed by Democratic Party Leaders|website=David Zuckerman for Governor|date=March 12, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Faisal Gill]], former chair of the Vermont Democratic Party\n* [[Scudder Parker]], former chair of the Vermont Democratic Party and Vermont state senator\n* Cindy Metcalf, former chair of the Vermont Democratic Party and chief of staff for Lieutenant Governor Racine\n\n;Individuals\n* [[Ben Cohen (businessman)|Ben Cohen]], co-founder of [[Ben & Jerry's]]<ref name=\"ben and jerry\">{{cite web|url=https://www.zuckermanforvt.com/news/2020/2/25/press-release-ben-and-jerry-endorse-david|title=Ben and Jerry Endorse David|website=David Zuckerman for Governor|date=February 23, 2020|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Jerry Greenfield]], co-founder of [[Ben & Jerry's]]<ref name=\"ben and jerry\"/>\n* [[Bill McKibben]], environmentalist, scholar at [[Middlebury College]], and leader of [[350.org]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.zuckermanforvt.com/news/